Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature in the software consumes more code than it should. For example, in the given class, when calling the 'baz' method in the 'bar' method, code assist replaces more code than necessary. The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me:

baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {
void bar(X x) {
baz(x.foo());
}
int foo() {
return 5;
}
void baz(int i, int j) {
}
